Author: davidw
Content: Sometimes I just don't know...  It's nice to work in the US for a lot of things - money first and foremost.  But San Jose is also a good example of what's unpleasant about the US.  Even a small town in Italy has (at least) an order of magnitude more character and interesting things, rather than sameness and right angles.  It's difficult if not impossible to attach a monetary value to, but I think there are definitely some externalities involved in living in a beautiful place, that at least for some people, compensate for the other things that are wrong.
